    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Radiation counters into which the sample is introduced in the form of a gas through the counter tube. The phenomenon of gas multiplication is used to increase pulse size which facilitates processing of the sample.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
